    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.15.14"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">240 Neihardt Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">14</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        1620 Pelham Road
                        Beechwood
                        Upper <unclear>Dally</unclear>
                        Pennsylvania
                        Dec 12 1930
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I'm writing to thank you for the kind word you <unclear/> for my book of poems not long back. I'm glad you liked Lonesome Water. Particularly <unclear/> from the first printing of your two earliest books by Mitchell Kennedy your work has meant something to me &#8212; and it seems to me in very different ways we're working toward a similar <unclear>end</unclear> &#8212; realizing the value of wholly American Themes for our art. My friend Henry Hart has shown me the letter you wrote him and it all the more has heightened my <unclear>wish</unclear> to meet you someday. Will you let me have that pleasure if you ever get East?</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Roy Helton</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Pasted inside <hi rend="underline">Lonesome Water</hi> &#8212; Roy Helton</note>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
